The paper focuses on computing equilibria in multiplayer games, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The algorithms used in the study are also related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The study involves analyzing the performance of algorithms on different games, which could fall under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
